@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<div style="text-align:center;">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <p>Last updated: April 7, 2026</p>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
        This application is an educational automaton simulator. We follow data minimization principles and process only
        the data required to provide core functionality such as authentication, saving automata, and collaboration features.
    </p>

    <h2>What Data We Process</h2>
    <ul style="list-style-position: inside; padding-left: 0;">
        <li>Account data: email and authentication-related identifiers.</li>
        <li>User content: automata definitions, execution states, and shared workspace metadata.</li>
        <li>Technical data: basic logs for reliability, diagnostics, and security monitoring.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Use Data</h2>
    <ul style="list-style-position: inside; padding-left: 0;">
        <li>Provide and secure the service.</li>
        <li>Store and restore automata and simulation state.</li>
        <li>Enable sharing and collaboration features.</li>
        <li>Diagnose errors and improve reliability.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>
        We do not sell personal data. Data may be shared only with service providers required for hosting and operations,
        or when legally required.
    </p>

    <h2>Retention</h2>
    <p>
        Data is retained only as long as needed for service operation, legal obligations, and security requirements.
        Users can request deletion of stored account-related data where applicable.
    </p>

    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p>
        We apply standard security practices such as authentication controls, least-privilege access, transport encryption,
        and monitoring. No method of transmission or storage is perfectly secure.
    </p>

    <h2>Your Rights</h2>
    <p>
        Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete your personal data.
        Contact the project owner to request support for these actions.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
        For privacy questions, please use the repository contact channels in the project page.
    </p>
</div>
